sql:
SELECT color_id
FROM color_usage
WHERE usage_count = (SELECT MAX(usage_count) FROM color_usage);

external_knowledge:
The 'birth years of the millennial generation' refer to the years 1990 to 2000;
The 'most popular garb' in this context corresponds to the color with the highest usage count for each vehicle model within the specified production years;
The 'predominant hue' means the color that was used most frequently.

sql:
SELECT SUM(price) AS TotalPrice
FROM vehicle_colors
WHERE availability_start_date <= '1992-12-31' AND availability_end_date >= '1991-01-01';
